## 1. Why do you use EKS instead of ECS?

I use Amazon Web Services EKS when the project requires:

* Kubernetes ecosystem and portability across cloud/on-prem
* Helm charts, Operators, service mesh, autoscaling
* Multi-cloud or hybrid-cloud support
* Better control over networking and orchestration

I use ECS when:

* The application is simple containerized workload
* Team wants less operational overhead
* Tight AWS integration is enough
* Faster deployment with lower management effort is needed

So, EKS is preferred for enterprise-grade Kubernetes environments, while ECS is good for simpler AWS-native container deployments.

