## 10. Difference between CMD and RUN in Docker

| RUN                         | CMD                            |
| --------------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| Executes during image build | Executes when container starts |
| Used to install packages    | Used to start application      |
| Multiple RUN allowed        | Usually one CMD                |
| Creates image layers        | Does not create build layer    |

Example:

```dockerfile
RUN apt-get update
CMD ["nginx", "-g", "daemon off;"]
```

